<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM VETERANS WALL</font><br>
<tt>Wed Nov 27  2:01:27 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I served in the infantry in 1969, 101st Airborne Division.  Now my family has given me a license-plate frame that says &quot;I carried an M-16 up Hamburger Hill&quot;.  I know that nobody behind my car will ever have any idea at all what that means, except for that one-in-a-million guy that was behind me on that hill and now is behind me in his car.  I feel the same about the Wall.  I was able to go only to a traveling replica of it.  I touched the engraved name of my best friend and of course, I cried.  But I still felt that only those who were there in the middle of it would ever really understand.  Because we who were there don't really understand it very well.  
<p><code>-- Graham@community.net  (Kelly Graham) </code><p>


